However, as we know from being human, every person is nuanced and unique, hence the value of the biopsychosocial model and flexibility within treatment settings despite the diagnoses. According to the American Psychological Association (
         2005
      ), the APA Council of Representatives released a statement in 2005 underscoring the importance of utilizing evidence-based practice in the treatment of disorders, which encompasses research evidence with patient values, strengths, personality, and sociocultural context.
